&lt;h1&gt;Staff Nurse (Nights)&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a Staff Nurse to join the Wirral Community Night Nursing Team. You should be a committed, dynamic, motivated professional having excellent assessing skills, the ability to prioritise your work and be a good communicator.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Recent experience of working in a similar environment would be an advantage. Awareness of Community Nursing, the effects of ill health, the ageing process and a basic level of IT literacy are an essential requirement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a key member of the team you will find the experience challenging, rewarding and varied.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Employment in this post requires an Enhanced Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) check.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to be able to work autonomously and as part of a team and possess excellent time management, organisational and communication skills. You will be innovative, flexible and prepared to adapt to the changing needs of the Trust as they arise.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ann Bayley on 0151 514 6677&lt;/p&gt;
